LabReport.comments: TEST INFORMATION: Vitamin D, 1,25-Dihydroxy This test is primarily indicated during patient evaluation for hypercalcemia and renal failure. A normal result does not rule out Vitamin D deficiency. The recommended test for diagnosing Vitamin D deficiency is Vitamin D 25-hydroxy (0080379).
